{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cb02794f-1a2b-47df-88f2-7553dcfaec26","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**MSTest v3 dropped support for older TFMs.** It requires:\n- **.NET Framework 4.6.2+** — your `net462` target is fine ✅\n- **.NET 6.0+** — your `net5.0` ❌ and `netcoreapp3.1` ❌ targets are **not supported**\n\nBoth `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` are end-of-life and were removed from MSTest v3's supported matrix.\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n1. Replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or `net8.0`)\n2. Replace `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0` (or `net8.0`)\n3. Update MSTest packages to v3 (e.g., switch to the unified `MSTest` meta-package)\n\nWould you like me to update the project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"398e6709-391e-4a50-a93a-d92952a34751","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They're using MSTest v2 (2.2.10) and want to migrate to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me recall the compatibility details:\n\n- MSTest v3 requires at minimum:\n  - .NET 6.0+ (for .NET Core/5+)\n  - .NET Framework 4.6.2+ (this should be fine since they target net462)\n  \nWait, actually let me think more carefully. MSTest v3 (the MSTest meta-package) dropped support for:\n\n\n- `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` since they're both out of support\n- But it does support .NET Framework 4.6.2 and later, plus .NET 6.0 and later\n\nSo the user would run into compatibility issues with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` — they'd need to either drop those target frameworks or stick with MSTest v2.","outputTokens":588,"requestId":"480B:A96C7:62AFD6A:6B069C3:69FBFD5B"},"id":"bf3ccd5c-5a2f-4db4-ab41-b65b320cab67","timestamp":"2026-05-07T02:48:08.793Z","parentId":"97daba36-8b3a-4513-b0c8-b4d768532737"}
